{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:10:19.738Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoding Categoricals"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of converting categorical (non-numeric) variables into numerical format that machine learning models can process — since models can only train on floating-point values and cannot understand strings like \"dog\" or \"maple,\" we must transform categories into numerical vectors."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Encoding is Necessary"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Core problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computers only process numbers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → models cannot train on strings\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Categorical data represents finite discrete values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → categories, labels, or types\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Machine learning requires numerical input"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → must convert categories to numbers"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What is categorical data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Qualitative data divided into distinct groups or categories\n- Examples: gender, color, product type, country, language"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Types of Categorical Variables"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Definition"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Nominal"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Categories without intrinsic order"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gender (Male, Female), Color (Red, Blue, Green), Race, Languages"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ordinal"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Categories with meaningful order/hierarchy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Education (High School, Bachelor's, Master's), Rating (Poor, Fair, Good, Excellent)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key difference"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Nominal variables have no order → need special encoding; Ordinal variables have order → can use ordinal encoding."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Encoding Categoricals — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "One-Hot Encoding"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Dummy Encoding)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Nominal variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (no order)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Converts each category to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "binary column"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that takes value 0 or 1."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How One-Hot Encoding Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Color variable with categories Red, Blue, Green"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Before:\n  Color\n  Red\n  Blue\n  Green\n\nAfter (One-Hot):\n  Color_Red  Color_Blue  Color_Green\n  1          0           0\n  0          1           0\n  0          0           1"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Process"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Each unique category → separate boolean column\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1 or True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = category present\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "0 or False"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = category absent"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use One-Hot Encoding"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Nominal variables"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No ordinal relationship exists"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low cardinality"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Few categories (e.g., gender, color)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Avoid hierarchy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ensure no order among categories"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Avoid"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- ❌ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High-cardinality variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., ZIP codes) → creates too many columns\n- ❌ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ordinal variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → destroys meaningful order"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python Implementation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Using scikit-learn\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder\n\nencoder = OneHotEncoder(drop='first')  # Drop first column to avoid redundancy\nX_encoded = encoder.fit_transform(X)\n\n# Using Pandas\nimport pandas as pd\n\ndf_encoded = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=['Color'], prefix=['Color'])\n# Or drop first column\ndf_encoded = pd.get_dummies(df, drop_first=True)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Insight: Drop First Column"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Avoids "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "dummy variable trap"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (multicollinearity)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If you have 6 categories in \"brand\" column, encoder returns 6 columns. But you can drop 1 column (first) and still have all information — reduces to 5 columns without losing information."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Label Encoding"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ordinal variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (has order)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Assigns a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "unique integer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to each category."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Label Encoding Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Color variable"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Before:\n  Color\n  Red\n  Blue\n  Green\n\nAfter (Label Encoding):\n  Color\n  0\n  1\n  2"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mapping"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- \"Red\" → 0\n- \"Blue\" → 1\n- \"Green\" → 2"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Label Encoding"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ordinal variables"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Order matters (e.g., Poor→0, Good→1, Excellent→2)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binary categories"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only two levels (e.g., Male→0, Female→1)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tree-based models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can work better than one-hot even without order"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem with nominal variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- ❌ Introduces "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ordinality where none exists"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (misleads model)\n- ❌ Example: \"Good=1, Average=0, Poor=2\" → artificial order not preserved"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual Ordinal Encoding (Preserving Order)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For ordinal variables where you want to preserve hierarchy:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import pandas as pd\n\n# Define order manually\nsize_order = {'Small': 0, 'Medium': 1, 'Large': 2}\n\n# Apply using replace function\ndf['Size_Encoded'] = df['Size'].map(size_order)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Python"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n\nencoder = LabelEncoder()\ny_encoded = encoder.fit_transform(y)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ordinal Encoding"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ordinal variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": " where order matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Similar to label encoding but explicitly preserves hierarchical order."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Ordinal Encoding"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Education levels"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High Sch